The paper presents a novel method for instance segmentation using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves predicting dense local shape descriptors, which is a form of feature engineering and could also fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using a neural network to learn the shape descriptors, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates the method on various microscopy datasets, which could fall under neural engineering (cs.NE) or multimedia (cs.MM).
